Coloration . Body coloration when chromatophores are contracted (
Fig. 22
) are light red with second, third and sixth abdominal pleomeres having transverse light red bands postertiorly; carapace laterally red, spines along cervical, postcervical groove red. Tips of dactyli, fixed fingers of third pereiopod white, rest of propodus, carpus and merus orange, ischium pink. Antennae and other appendages semitransparent, pinkish. Posterior half of telson, uropods red. Body coloration and most appendages when chromatophores are expanded (
Fig. 23
) bright red. Middle of fourth, sixth abdominal pleomeres, and anterior half of telson white. Third pereiopod tips of dactyli and fixed finger white, rest of propodus, carpus, and merus pink, ischium red; eyes golden brown.
